  "body": "Since a few days back, I'm seeing an increase in the input bandwidth. The input and output rates are diverging as you can see in this graph. The scale is a big off due to the event marked there, but the two lines are clearly separating with the input one having increased about 30% while the output less than 10%\r\n\r\n\r\n![fo](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16044918/124750886-630f3d00-defc-11eb-96fb-9712da928339.jpg)\r\n\r\nThis is a dedicated server running:\r\n-  Arch linux 5.12.12-x86_64 \r\n- `beacon-chain version Prysm/v1.3.9/255354f27eb9cdd7d3afe5ef9759629150785276` and same commit for the validator client. \r\n- Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-8259U CPU @ 2.30GHz\r\n- 64GB DDR4 RAM\r\n- 2Tb NVME",
